WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.820
So I'm going to talk about a much smaller trial, phase one clinical trial, looking at

00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:09.060
BFR-Cartesal therapy for B-cell non-herting lymphoma.

00:00:09.640 --> 00:00:12.440
All the data show here are patients treated at City of Hope.

00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:20.560
So just, I think we probably, most of us know that, no doubt, that Cartesal has already

00:00:20.560 --> 00:00:25.320
resulted in landscape changes in how we treat patients with aggressive B-cell lymphoma.

00:00:25.780 --> 00:00:31.760
From ZOMA 7, we know there's overall survival benefits, and PFS is also outperformed the

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:35.820
standard care at the time, salvage chemo plus transplant.

00:00:36.480 --> 00:00:38.240
So PFS is 42%.

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:40.660
This is with a median for about four years.

00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.500
That means that more than 50% of patients still will not have a durable remission, and

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:49.800
there's still room to go for us how to manage those patients.

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:55.540
And the main reason for those patients who did not survive after four years or they

00:00:55.540 --> 00:00:55.600
procrastinated.

00:00:55.780 --> 00:00:59.100
The cause of death is really progression of disease.

00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:06.960
So one of the major resistance mechanisms for this CAR to fail is really antigen loss

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:08.780
or antigen down-modulation.

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:13.560
So once you have the CAR, it could persist, but if the antigen is not there, then the

00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:14.400
CAR wouldn't work.

00:01:14.780 --> 00:01:18.140
Now, there are many different approaches to get around this, make your CAR more potent

00:01:18.140 --> 00:01:24.600
by adding a cytokine or other immune modulator, or as we learned about, dual targeting, so

00:01:24.600 --> 00:01:25.760
multi-agent targeting.

00:01:25.780 --> 00:01:30.400
So if you can't do multi-agent targeting, then it's really difficult to really get around

00:01:30.400 --> 00:01:31.500
one antigen loss.

00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:36.400
But there's another way to think about this, is what about an alternative antigen target,

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:42.060
a target that it'll be more difficult for the tumor cell to down-regulate or to lose?

00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:46.780
So the molecule that we are interested in is called BAF-R.

00:01:46.780 --> 00:01:53.600
BAF-R is a receptor that once it's upon binding with BAF, BAF actually binds to BAF-R, BCMA,

00:01:53.600 --> 00:01:54.600
and then BF-R.

00:01:54.600 --> 00:01:55.600
It's a receptor.

00:01:55.600 --> 00:02:03.720
So BAF-R's main function in B cell development is B cell maturation, differentiation, and

00:02:03.720 --> 00:02:07.420
also, more importantly, it delivers a survival signal.

00:02:07.420 --> 00:02:11.320
And the BAF-R expression on the right side is on the top line.

00:02:11.320 --> 00:02:15.640
So it's not really, it doesn't start with a pre-pro-B cell stage.

00:02:15.640 --> 00:02:21.320
It gets to the immature transition of B cells and all the way into the cell becoming plasma

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:22.320
cells.

00:02:22.320 --> 00:02:24.420
So it's a very short duration.

00:02:24.420 --> 00:02:29.000
But it is a B cell delinquent marker.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:36.320
And in tumor cells, the mental cell lymphoma cells, or lymphoblastic leukemia cells, BAF-R

00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:39.380
is actually also required for tumor survival.

00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:45.240
And we look at BAF-R expression on the abnormal lymphoid cells, that is, the mental cell lymphoma,

00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:48.040
CLL, DLB cell, follicular, and marginal zone.

00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:51.540
So it's pretty broadly expressed.

00:02:51.540 --> 00:02:52.540
And we have done research.

00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:53.540
Now, we demonstrated that.

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:53.540
When you have a B cell delinquent marker, there is a B cell delinquent marker.

00:02:53.540 --> 00:02:54.020
And if you have a B cell delinquent marker, there is a B cell delinquent marker.

00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:54.040
And if you have a B cell delinquent marker, there is a B cell delinquent marker.

00:02:54.040 --> 00:02:54.420
And if you have a B cell delinquent marker, there is a B cell delinquent marker.

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:59.420
And in leukemia cells or lymphoma cells that are deficient in CD19, they still preserve

00:02:59.420 --> 00:03:01.080
their BAF-R expression.

00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:06.540
And here's just one preclinical study demonstrating that the same vector, different target, BAF-R,

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:13.040
or CD19, in this setting, the BAF-R CAR-T really outperforms the CD19 CAR-T's activities

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:14.540
in the tumor model.

00:03:14.540 --> 00:03:18.960
And it's not because of antigen density, because the BAF-R expression level is much lower than

00:03:18.960 --> 00:03:21.720
CD19 on these target cells.

00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:24.020
So based on this, Larry Quagg has said, "I'm not sure if this is true."

00:03:24.020 --> 00:03:28.900
Larry Quagg has said, "I hope we design a BAF-R CAR-T together with our CAR-T group's

00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:29.900
effort."

00:03:29.900 --> 00:03:35.940
So it's based on the antibody that derived from his research laboratory.

00:03:35.940 --> 00:03:43.300
So we designed a phase one clinical trial to test these CAR-Ts in the patient with B

00:03:43.300 --> 00:03:44.300
cells.

00:03:44.300 --> 00:03:48.420
Now, host cell lymphoma, they need to have BAF-R expression either based on flow or based

00:03:48.420 --> 00:03:53.620
on HC, and this assay was developed as a companion assay, and it's pretty standard.

00:03:53.620 --> 00:04:00.460
on CAR-T treatment schema here. And here I'm showing the patient characteristics from eight

00:04:00.460 --> 00:04:05.720
patients. So we had treated nine patients there, but there are some data not available. Therefore,

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:10.780
I'm only showing some results from first eight patients. And the first three patients received

00:04:10.780 --> 00:04:17.440
15 million dose level one, and then you escalated to 200 million CAR-T dose. So six patients were

00:04:17.440 --> 00:04:23.260
treated at the dose level two. And look at all those patients, most of them are mental cell

00:04:23.260 --> 00:04:29.380
lymphoma patients. One patient has T cell history, B cell lymphoma, 19 and 20 negative.

00:04:30.060 --> 00:04:35.680
5.8 patients already have prior signaling in CAR-T cell treatment. And four of the MCR patients

00:04:35.680 --> 00:04:41.960
had TP3 mutation. So I hope you agree with me, this is not a very easy patient population to

00:04:41.960 --> 00:04:47.420
treat. So we, you know, the data actually look pretty safe in this patient. At most,

00:04:47.440 --> 00:04:53.100
patient will have a great one second release syndrome. Patient used to, you know, either they

00:04:53.100 --> 00:04:59.840
get tocilizumab, no one gets any dexamethasone and result within just a few days. And ICANs only

00:04:59.840 --> 00:05:06.680
occur in two out of eight patients, all in dose level one, and that's around a day, and no one

00:05:06.680 --> 00:05:13.660
needed any intervention. And here's the clinical efficacy. All the patients, you know, seven out

00:05:13.660 --> 00:05:17.320
of seven first treated patients received a complete remission, and they

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:22.220
continued staying remission. The one that being remission for more than three years is the top,

00:05:22.380 --> 00:05:28.540
the first patient. So looking at the CAR-T expansion, so all patients now had

00:05:28.540 --> 00:05:34.000
pretty high levels of CAR-T expansion. And the peak of expansion is actually in the second week

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:40.820
of the CAR-T infusion. And this is supported by both by flow cytometry study and also WPIE.

00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:47.420
And this is like I throw in there, just we have now CD19 CAR-T expansion data from two of the

00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:54.140
patients who had prior CD19 CAR-Ts compared. So compared to CD19 CAR-T expansion versus the

00:05:54.140 --> 00:06:01.320
by far CAR-T expansion over time, they clearly by far CAR-T is expanding much higher and also

00:06:01.320 --> 00:06:06.900
peak level is also much higher. And this is a study we used to look at the manufacturing

00:06:06.900 --> 00:06:11.980
products activities from all the first six patients. All patients had complete remission,

00:06:11.980 --> 00:06:17.280
and based on this polyfunctional strength index, which is really simultaneously looking at

00:06:17.440 --> 00:06:22.980
cytokine production, looking at proliferation, and looking at CAR-T, you know, the product's

00:06:22.980 --> 00:06:30.400
performance. Now, all six products has great performance. And I'm going to have a minute.

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:35.920
So this is a patient who had multiple lines of prior therapy, around 10 lines of prior therapy,

00:06:36.140 --> 00:06:40.900
mental cell lymphoma. Now, his treatment course really is like telling a story how we manage

00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:45.960
mental cell lymphoma over the years. The patient had, you know, by specific patient had row one

00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:51.360
rectal cells. Actually, the first one who got rectal cells, CTL-HOLD, but unfortunately

00:06:51.360 --> 00:06:58.080
didn't stay in remission long enough. So the patient was enrolled into the study. He actually

00:06:58.080 --> 00:07:03.300
tolerated the treatment really well. And we look at the bone marrows. Now, after the post-CAR-T

00:07:03.300 --> 00:07:09.200
treatment, the one on the right lower panel, now all the by far positive cells were gone.

00:07:09.640 --> 00:07:16.160
And we look at this, the UMAP, looking at different populations over time. Now, the bright green one

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:21.420
here, the CAR-T cells, you see the CAR-T cell continue to expand throughout the time. You know,

00:07:21.460 --> 00:07:26.680
it really gets out around day nine and continues through day 28. And there are also a minor

00:07:26.680 --> 00:07:34.980
population of CD4 CAR-Ts there. And so the plan for this study is we already decided to use 200

00:07:34.980 --> 00:07:41.960
milling as the RP2D instead of further escalate to those level three. And this study now becoming

00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:46.560
a multi-center study for our phase two expansion cohort. And in addition,

00:07:47.440 --> 00:07:55.540
CAR-T is also evaluated in a phase one clinical trial for a patient with beta-ALL. Thank you.
